  },
  {
    id: 'liquid-cooling',
    icon: 'water_drop',
    title: 'Liquid Cooling Infrastructure',
    summary: 'Coolant distribution leaks and thermal inefficiency detected across campus.',
    description: 'As rack densities push beyond 40kW toward 140kW+ for AI workloads, liquid cooling is becoming standard — but brings new failure modes. Manifold connection points, quick-disconnect fittings, and CDU piping are vulnerable to micro-leaks that reduce flow efficiency and raise internal temperatures. Coolant chemistry degradation creates corrosion and biofilm risks that clog microchannels. Our aerial thermal imaging detects these thermal anomalies across exterior cooling loops, CDU arrays, and distribution piping before a single leak becomes a cascade failure.',
    detection: 'Radiometric thermal mapping of exterior cooling loops with AI classification of leak signatures, flow imbalances, and coolant degradation patterns.',
